  <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Preliminary assessment of ex-vessel waveguides for the ITER Plasma Position Reflectometer</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="260" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="c">2017-03-19</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">• Tentative waveguide technologies are evaluated for the ex-vessel transmission line of the ITER Plasma Position reflectometer using the current space reservation models. • Both rectangular waveguides and circular corrugated waveguides are analyzed for different dimensions fitting in the models. • Preliminary results for ohmic and mitre bend losses are calculated using previous literature results. • In-depth analyses, using more accurate methods, were performed on selected waveguides, for ohmic losses, gap losses and mode conversion in mitre bends. • Results led to choose 88.9 mm circular corrugated waveguide for the ex-vessel transmission lines of the PPR.</subfield>
